{meta: artist The Gibson Brothers}
{meta: composer Eric Gibson and Joe Newberry}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]We went upon the mountain to hear the old man [F]pray
And [G7]everything about him was steeped in the old time [C]way
The sound he made was strange it was magic it was [F]fun
When [G7]asked when it was come back when he smiled as said [C]son
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
They called it [G7]music in the church house in the fields
It was [F]honest it was simple and it [C]helped the part time chill
It was [G7]music singing deep down in the mines
In the [F]dark and lonesome prison cells and [G7]behind battle lines
They called it [C]music
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
